spanGrp.span: Me, I will tell my story as I am here with Richard
mimi nitazungumza hadithi yangu nikiwa na Richard
I was a woman, I got up and went to Matala
aqawasch qarm qang'ech aa gawa matal
nikiwa mwanamke niliamka na kwenda matala
I went to greet my older sister
nitaenda kumsalimia mkubwa wangu wa kike
I went and slept on the route
And the next day I arrived at two in the afternoon
na kesho yake nikafika saa nane
Ah, that is, Matala is far, uh
Matala by foot is very far, when I arrived that day, I was walking with my knees, I couldn't even stand, I couldn't stand easily
shag matal ab geshang diya ii gamuch aa gadugunyaday ab burand yaani mamus ar gidab gidang'et yaani gang'et shid
'''shag matal ab geshang diya ii gamuch aa gadugunyaday ab burand yaani mamus ar gidab gidang''''et yaani gang''''et shid'''
matala kwa miguu ni mbali sana nilipofika siku ile mimi nilikuea nikitembea kwa magoti hata kusimama siwezi nasimama kwa shida
I can't sleep, when it was the next day my sister gave me water and I bathed, when she was done she cooked and...
mamus galililj gamuch aa goshang'shang'nan dada edeny beg aa gahush am hit gowosh aa qo
'''mamus galililj gamuch aa goshang''''shang''''nan dada edeny beg aa gahush am hit gowosh aa qo..'''
siwezi nililala ilipokucha dada yangu alinipashia maji nikaoga alipomaliza akapika na....
She prepared food and we ate
Iiih, that is, Matala is very far, by foot
ii na aashag matal ab geshang aashag diya
ii na aashag matal ab geshang aashag diya
iih yaani matala ni mbali sana eti kwa miguu
But not often they don't go by foot, they go by car or by motorcycle
qamn ad madebadinew geshang gebadinew garajeg aa bigbikajeg
qamn ad madebadinew geshang gebadinew garajeg aa bigbikajeg
lakini sasa hivi huwa hawaendi tena kwa miguu wanaenda kwa gari na kwa pikipiki
Another day I went to Dugwamuhosht
I went and walked to the top of a hill
gaw dugmuhosht aa gawayaday aa uudgijeeda
gaw dugmuhosht aa gawayaday aa uudgijeeda
nilienda na nilitembea juu ya mlima
Eight in the morning until I descended it was
ba ijeny aa dararang'an aset ba
saa mbili hadi nikashuka ilipotimu saa
I walked until I slept in Gidoskweeda
I slept in Gidoskweeda and the next day I left
galil ab gidoskwed aa gamuch aa gawi
galil ab gidoskwed a gamuch aa gawi
nikalala gidoskweda na kesho yake nikaondoka
I went to sleep in Gidabugeeg, and I tell you it is far
gawa aa gakil aa gidibuger na ang'ing' ashagi ii
'''gawa aa gakil aa gidibuger na ang''''inf'''' ashagi ii'''
nikaenda nikalala gidabuger na kwambia ni mbali
We walked until we reached Dugwamuhosht, it was four in the afternoon
gewayadi gichaehit dugmuhosht gehit sa kumi
gewayadi gichaehit dugmuhosht gehit sa kumi
tukatembea kufika dugamuhosht ni saa kumi
It's very far, and I was very tired
ii ashag diya qahit aa gaburej gichgichi
ii ashag diya qahit aa gaburej gichgichi
ni mbali sana nilifika nikiwa nimechoka
I told my sister, you came here to leave here?
gayesh dada na ginuny aa many hij
gayesh dada na ginuny aa many hij
nikamwambia dada yangu hivi ulikuja na kuishi hapo
What thing drove you away so that you came to move here?
uu naqahoneny naha aa many howanji
uu naqahoneny naha aa many howanji
hivi kitu gani kilikufukuza hadi unakuja kuhamia huku
She told me it was just migration
She got up and got me bathing water, and I bathed in her home, people lived in a small house, and it was created with wood and grass on top
qang'et aa goshang'shang'nan beg aa gahushi qaredany abita buned gobit itembajeg sisinew gediga aa gerams nyega
'''qang''''et aa goshang''''shang''''nan beg aa gahushi qaredany abita buned gobit itembajeg sisinew gediga aa gerams nyega'''
akaamka na akanipashia maji ya kuoga nami nikaoga kwenye nyumba yake watu wanaishi kwenye nyumba za tembe na imetengetezwa kwa miti na juu yake imewekwa nyasi
And the house was swept with a brush made out of branches
aa gebus galg gebus fagiyajeg madaq mandan gelaku gedig aa gebusew
aa gebus galg gebus fagiyajeg madaq mandan gelaku gedig aa gebusew
na nyumba zinafagiwa kwa ufagio wa miti
People often prepared skins to sleep on
Often they prepare a bed of brances and sleep on top of it
gesisin sisind gedig aa gelil ab wud
gesisin sisind gedig aa gelil ab wud
huwa wanatengeneza kitanda cha miti na kulala juu yake
They sleep on top of the branches
aa buneed gwaroch ud gedig aa hiji
aa buneed gwaroch ud gedig aa hiji
watu wanalalaga juu ya miti hapo
That is, in our lives, we have come a long way
ii yani maish geang'eadew ed shag diya yani shag aa shag aa shag diya
'''ii yani maish geang''''edw ed shag diya yani shag aa shag aa shag diya'''
That is, I saw people, they were in the bush, in the mountains with many trees
yaani buneed qaday gwand porin jeed gijeeg jeej gedig sang' diya
'''yaani buneed qaday gwand porin jeed gijeeg jeej gedig sang'''' diya'''
yaani ninaona watu wapo porini kwenye milima na miti mingi sana
We were in the forest, in the forest, there was no beginning
gend darabet darabet mand qut yani
gend darabet darabet mand qut yani
tupo msituni kwenye msitu usio na mwanzo
That is, I was surprised, a child from Mang'ola
ii anin galasay gew jaft lab mang'ol
'''ii anin galasay gew jaft lab mang''''ol'''
'''yaani mimi nilishangaa sana mtoto niliyetoka mang''''ola'''
